==English==
===Adjective===
'''neutral'''

# Not taking sides in a conflict such as war; [[unaligned]].
# Favouring neither the supporting nor opposing viewpoint of a topic of debate; [[unbiased]].
# Neither beneficial nor harmful.
# Neither [[positive]] nor [[negative]]; possessing no [[charge]] or equivalent positive and negative charge such that there is no imbalance.
# Having a [[pH]] of 7, neither [[acidic]] nor [[alkaline]].
# ([[Weather]]) When the [[temperature]] of the [[ground]] is [[approximately]] the same as the temperature of the lower air up to 4 meters (13.12 Feet) above it. This condition has light to [[moderate]] [[winds]], and [[slight]] [[turbulence]], and is considered [[average]] for the release of [[chemical agents]].

